                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top left corner, National Library book label with the current signum. Top of page, in black ink by a medieval hand: <quote>Liber Sententiarum Magistri petri lombardi</quote>.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Tan leather over bevelled wooden boards. 8 double raised bands and endbands. Originally, 2 pin clasps with leather straps. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, in black ink: <quote>28</quote>; stamped in gold: <quote>A 150</quote>; on a paper label, Jaches's signum in brown ink: <quote>25</quote>; on a paper label, Hammarsköld's signum in brown ink:<quote> e.30.3. 12</quote>; remnants of a paper label with writing visible underneath.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="375" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="270" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="100" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather worn with a few holes, wormholes, and tears around <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>; corners, top of <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, and section of <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/> repaired with brown leather patches. Clasps and straps missing; holes from 2 pins.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>Origin unknown. <origDate notAfter="1275" notBefore="1226">13th century, middle</origDate> (cf. <bibl>
                                    <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107302">Bieniak </title>
                                    <citedRange from="117" to="117" unit="page"/>
                                    <citedRange from="23" to="23" unit="footnote"/>
                                </bibl>). According to Lehtinen, the manuscript is an apopecia (<bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107313">Lehtinen (1999–2000)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="31" to="31" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>), which together with the early date and the layout would point to <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100064">Paris</placeName> as the place of origin.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript carries the marks of several of its previous owners (see Additions).</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>It is not known how tha manuscript came to the <orgName>National Library</orgName>. It is first mentioned in Jache's catalogue of 1698 (U 122) and listed there as no. <quote>25</quote>. Before 1698, the manuscript, according to a former librarian, had the signum <quote>192</quote>, listed on the now damaged paper label on the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>. It is listed in Hammarsköld’s catalogue from the 19th century (U 133) as <quote>e.30.3.12</quote>. The signum <quote>28</quote>, found on the <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, has not been identified.</p>
                        </acquisition>
                    </history>
