                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Index of Questiones, part 2</title>
                                <note>Index of Hugh of Saint-Cher's commentary on Book II, distinctio 40 - Book IV, distinctio 49 of Lombard's Sentences, listing the numbers and topics of the distinctiones.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="3r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Quodlibetal questions</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the resurrection</title>
                                    <incipit>Utrum surrectio sit naturalis</incipit>
                                    <explicit>ut ergo omnes elementi resurgerent tribus diebus retardauit surreccionem</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the sacraments</title>
                                    <incipit>Sacramentum est sacrum rei signum</incipit>
                                    <explicit>ut dicat hec non posse iustificari tum hiis cum ab hiis percipiendis ar<unclear quantity="4" unit="chars"/> necessitatis excludet</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <note>Dispersed throughout the manuscript are 18 quodlibetal questions identified and partially edited by <bibl>
                                        <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107307">Stegmüller</title>
                                    </bibl>.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107307">Stegmüller (1949)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="203" to="205" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102595"> Bernard of Clairvaux </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Liber de consideratione, excerpts</title>
                                <rubric>Beatus Bernardus libro <num type="ordinal" value="4">iiii<hi rend="super">o</hi>
                                    </num> de consideratione</rubric>
                                <incipit>sollerter aduertas vir sagacissime Eugeni</incipit>
                                <explicit>facit affectio sancta quasi <!--?--> sanctus timor amor</explicit>
                                <note>The main text consists of excerpts from Book V of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102595">St Bernard</persName>'s Liber de consideratione, after which are added two brief excerpts from <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102515"> St Augustine</persName>'s. De Genesi ad litteram libri duodecim, Book 12, Chapter 14.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="alt" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">Patrologia Latina</title>
                                    <citedRange from="182" to="182" unit="volume"/>
                                    <citedRange from="787" to="806" unit="column"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Quodlibetal questions</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On free will</title>
                                    <incipit>quaestio de libero arbitrio primo si est</incipit>
                                    <explicit>patet ergo utrumque sed non est ad utrumque ut li ad ordinationem dicat</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On beatific vision</title>
                                    <incipit>questio est de quolibet primo utrum sit eadem uisio uie et patrie</incipit>
                                    <explicit>multa possunt esse media propter hoc non secunda item de tertio</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Miscellaneous quodlibetal questions</title>
                                    <incipit>questio est de quolibet primo de questione morali</incipit>
                                    <explicit>Item est mensura rerum mutabilium solum</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Miscellaneous quodlibetal questions</title>
                                    <incipit>queritur de quolibet quare dominus maledixit ficum</incipit>
                                    <explicit>primitias nostre masse</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On God's immutability</title>
                                    <incipit>queritur de immutabilitate dei primo utrum <add place="above">insit</add>sibi soli</incipit>
                                    <explicit>sed in re suscipiente Nota li dominus diuinam dicit essentiam</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Quodlibetum of brother Gaufridus de Blenello</title>
                                    <incipit>Questio est de quolibet fratris gaufridi primo utrum sint plures ueritates ab eterno</incipit>
                                    <explicit>eterna pena punietur et hoc accidit ratione fori</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the incitement of the Devil</title>
                                    <incipit>serpens erat callidior</incipit>
                                    <explicit>ymaginatio non tantum est uisibilium sed audibilium</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the powers of the soul</title>
                                    <incipit>questio est utrum anima sit sue potencie vel non</incipit>
                                    <explicit>quod intelligit dicitur subiectum</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5va" to="5va" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the number of the divine persons</title>
                                    <incipit>faciamus hominem ad imaginem et cetera occasione horum verborum</incipit>
                                    <explicit>quod est extraneum a natura dei</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5va" to="5vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On the immortality of the soul</title>
                                    <incipit>questio est de immortalitate anime primo utrum sit mortalis per naturam</incipit>
                                    <explicit>cuius sunt duo opera uegetare et alimento uti</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="5vb" to="5vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On original sin</title>
                                    <incipit>queritur quid sit originale Respondeo idem est quod concupiscentia</incipit>
                                    <explicit>culpa esset si uellet(?) hoc su<unclear quantity="12" unit="chars"/>
                                    </explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107307">Stegmüller (1949)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="205" to="221" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="6r" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Index of Questiones, part 1</title>
                                <note>Index of Hugh of Saint-Cher's commentary on Book I, distinctio 1 – Book II, distinctio 38, of Lombard's Sentences, listing the numbers and topics of the distinctiones.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
